Current earnings and net income from financial transactions fell to zero compared to the same period of the previous year, while earnings from exposures and certain securities, as well as from the dissolution of provisions in the credit business, fell by more than 70 percent to EUR 5 million.
Only thanks to higher income from reimbursements of downstream settlement costs from the restructuring of the former Depfa Group as well as from the reimbursement of interest under the Tax Code and from the business provision for group companies, the earnings downside at around 16 percent had been moderate.
