Her dancing was sensual and I have been told that my dancing is also in this aesthetic area," she claims.
The production expects two extraordinary collaborations: with Miguel Poveda, who will sing again for Isabel at one of her performances, as he did in La puerta abierta; and with flamenco master Matilde Coral, who wanted to work exceptionally together with one of her ex-students.
<0x60>Matilde plays Tórtola, a very mature personality.
I'm happy because she agreed to be involved in my work, and I'm very honored."
