Democratic MP Brad Sherman, who heads a group in Congress called “the caucus of skeptics,” portrays things differently, but comes to the same conclusion.
“Four hundred distinguished professors of economics, including three Nobel laureates, have written to us to tell us that we are asking Congress not to be put under pressure and to carefully consider what path to take,” he said.
