Today, the European Summit on Equal Opportunities started in Paris, hosted this year by France, the EU Presidency of the Council.
In her address to the plenary, Fidesz Member of the European People’s Party, Lívia Járóka, called attention to the education segregation, which is one of the most serious violations of the law that Roma children face, and the biggest obstacle to their need for validity.
The high-level conference was opened by French Minister for Employment and Social Affairs, Xavier Bertrand, on behalf of the French Presidency, and Vladimir Spidla, EU Commissioner for Employment, Social Affairs and Equal Opportunities.
