All in all, there is now no more breakfast during working hours; stop with coffee or croissant.
Brunetta says with a smile: “A good cappuccino at 7 o’clock works wonders.”
During a meeting of the Superior Committee of Public Administration (Scuola Superiore della Pubblica Amministrazione)
The minister said that "within three months, the absences of officials have been reduced to 50%, that is, 60,000 more people per year are present at work".
He adds that it is necessary to strengthen the efficiency of Italy's public administration
"their wage dynamics - according to the minister - have been twice as large as the private sector in the last 8-10 years and far above the inflation rate".
