It is a problem that needs to be solved – according to the interviewed journalists – if one wants to prevent traditional journalism, as the large audience understands it, from shrinking substantially.
A clear but complicated pessimism nowadays fills the American journalist.
Six out of ten journalists and senior executives in the press believe that journalism at the national level is on the wrong track.
In the local area, executives are even around 65%.
Printed vs. Broadcast.
It is not difficult for journalists to imagine in which direction the web is going.
The most important publishing groups are making their way into the Internet, which is regarded by many as the "killer" of the printing press.
