The 500 interviewed journalists have admitted to joining the new technology in the hope that "they will bring something good for journalism."
The biggest rift in American journalism today is between the editors-in-chief of the newsroom and the reporters who work for them.
56% of editors-in-chief at national level are confident that their reporters share their values with them, whereas only 23% at local level.
